Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.55,0:00:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The most precious moment in life is the time of decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.37,0:00:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace, but it also leaves us with many lessons to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.27,0:00:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ketsudan (decision)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.27,0:00:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Use your wisdom Use your head Keep thinking it you're a man
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.13,0:00:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you cry or laugh, it depends on your decision
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.20,0:01:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be arrogant even if you win Don't cry even if you lose
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.06,0:01:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Man does not show tears
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.58,0:01:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Tatsunoko Production
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.99,0:01:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Final Decision (Episode 25)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.32,0:01:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,On the morning of April 27th, the UK, the US, China, a trilateral joint declaration was announced.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.94,0:01:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Potsdam Declaration.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.32,0:02:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This morning, Kantaro Suzuki, the president of the Information Bureau of the Cabinet
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.14,0:02:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and Hiroshi Shimomura admired the strength of the little bird that came to seek food even in the scorched earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.39,0:02:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,> Good morning > Good morning, Mr. Oyadomari.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.35,0:02:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,> Important news has arrived. > Important news?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.07,0:02:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,> At 6 o'clock this morning, San Francisco reported a declaration from the United States, the United Kingdom, and China.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.73,0:02:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,> The US, UK and China? Isn't it the US, UK, and Soviet Union? > It is in the US, UK and China. surely.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.39,0:02:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,> So what? > They demand unconditional surrender by Japan. It consists of 13 items.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.49,0:02:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,>It is almost the same as the Cairo Declaration. > That's right. What do you think? Not as an information officer, but as an individual.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.87,0:03:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,> It is the same as an individual and an Army intelligence officer. I should be silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.07,0:03:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,> I don't think so. > Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.90,0:03:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,> If you read it carefully, it is very hard on the war leaders, but respects the people and human rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.25,0:03:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,> It's just a ploy. > They are calling for surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.59,0:03:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,> Do you surrender to the US, UK and China?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.94,0:03:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,> That's right. Looking at the current leadership, no one has the courage to respond to this surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.80,0:03:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't know it's time to surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.66,0:04:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The Army is in a thorough fight, and the Cabinet is trying to avoid responsibility. If we do that, we lose our chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.39,0:04:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not only our chance, but more and more people are being killed while we dither.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.28,0:04:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The United States, dropped leaflets sown with bombs to inform the Japanese people of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.01,0:04:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the cabinet decided to kill this proclamation as a plot to upset the people and claim that the United States was impatient to collect its own station as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.59,0:04:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,> However, perhaps this problem is to well known to kill silently?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.42,0:05:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it would be suspicious to publish this important news in the newspaper without knowing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.45,0:05:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,> Is it? If so, I will respect the minister's opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.59,0:05:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If it is announced, it should be categorically criticized to prevent morale from deteriorating, and raise the fighting spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.28,0:05:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,> However, that would ruin the peace work that is currently underway through the Soviet Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.73,0:05:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,> What? Are you still doing peace work? > If you do not show your will to fight to the end, you cannot even make peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.11,0:05:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,> Despite the Soviet Union attending the Potsdam Conference, the Japanese government was still hoping for a peace treaty
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.94,0:05:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,through the Soviet Union and was negotiating through dispatches to Fumimaro Konoe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.18,0:05:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,> Captain Harry, Chief of Information for the United States, has declared that:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.76,0:06:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire population of Japan has become a front-line military target.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.80,0:06:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no non-combatants in Japan now. We seek to destroy the largest number of enemies, both men and women, in the shortest possible time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.35,0:06:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite this, the Japanese people are unaware of the situation. I think we need to let them know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.80,0:06:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In that regard, if you have any reason to oppose this, at your own discretion, please let me know in advance. It's a nuisance to the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.21,0:06:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,> Sir, What is nuisance? The people are happy to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.25,0:06:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,> What an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.21,0:06:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,> Since you are a private actor, you do not feel worried about the country. 1 don't work for you anymore. Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.39,0:06:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,> That's a problem. > There are more problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.66,0:07:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the mainland will be a battlefield, it will kill all the old people, children, and sick ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.59,0:07:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't think of anyone who is going to be more of a stumbling block then commanders of the Japanese army who says such things.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.32,0:07:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,> What? Do they, want to kill all our people? What do they mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.35,0:07:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,> As if to underline this claim, another calamity fell on the innocent people who are killed by both their enemies and allies.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.80,0:07:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,At 8:15 am on August 6th, 1945, the atomic bomb was dropped on Hiroshima for the first time in human history,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.04,0:07:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In an instant, 240,000 people were killed or injured there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.87,0:08:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A plutonium bomb was also dropped on Nagasaki around 11:00 am on August 9th. Here again, more than 100,000 people died in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.90,0:08:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What surprised the Japanese commanders more than that was the actions of the Soviet Union, which
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.76,0:08:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan had requested to mediate peace. Suddenly they had declared that they would participate in the war against Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.11,0:08:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The first Cabinet meeting since then was held on August 9th at 14:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.32,0:08:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,After explaining the current situation to Foreign Minister Togo, Prime Minister Kantaro Suzuki stood up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.32,0:08:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,> As Foreign Minister Togo said, things have become desperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.56,0:08:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to ask all of you for your opinions and to decide on a policy regarding the Tripartite Joint Declaration.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.52,0:09:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,> At present, no matter how much the three allied countries talk about the security of the imperial family and give favorable conditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.56,0:09:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,unconditional surrender is inevitable. Of course, with the atomic bomb and war with the Soviet Union, there is no prospect of victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.42,0:09:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,As we continue to fight for the honor of the Yamato people, we will have some chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.07,0:09:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask for the people's cooperation. If you come up with a tactic, I think there is a possibility that the battlefield situation will improve rather than us being completely defeated.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.45,0:09:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,> What is the chance of that? In particular. > A decisive battle on the mainland.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.90,0:09:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,> Only then will you have a chance. It's time to give the Army a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.01,0:10:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,> No, modern warfare cannot be done without the total backing of the nation. It's not a war that the Army or the Navy alone can win.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.56,0:10:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Prior to the the atomic bomb and the entering of the Soviet Union, there was no material for the war to continue in the current domestic situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.80,0:10:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, the Navy has no chance of winning against the US and UK.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.07,0:10:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,At this time, I am not particular about honor. I would like to stop this wishful thinking and have discussions in line with the actual situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.97,0:10:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,> Thus, regarding whether or not to accept the Trilateral Joint Declaration, the group wanting to accept with Foreign Minister Togo and the Navy Minister Yonai
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.11,0:10:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and the opposition group with the Minister of the Army, Anan, and the Minister of Munitions Toyoda will discuss long after 22:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.07,0:10:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,However, no conclusion could be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.11,0:11:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,> So what happened to the Cabinet decision? > We haven't come to a conclusion yet?.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.80,0:11:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,> By the way, what about you, Governor? Do you want to accept or do you oppose?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.07,0:11:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,> I have a personal opinion, But I'm spokesman for the cabinet. It is my job to give an opinion on behalf of the cabinet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.56,0:11:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,> More than that, when I came here, I was taught by looking at the cycads in front of the entrance of the Prime Ministers Office.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.42,0:11:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,> That big cycad.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.97,0:11:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,> After all, it was destroyed by air raids, and the leaves and trees were destroyed in bright red.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.52,0:12:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But when I look at it today, I noticed that blue sprouts are emerging from among the burnt trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.35,0:12:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese people are cycads. No matter what happens, someday new buds will come out again. We can't take the root. We have to leave them in any form.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.28,0:12:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,> Hmm. I will go soon. > What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.21,0:12:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,> From 23:50, the Supreme War Leaders’ Meeting will be held. > Is it from now on?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.87,0:12:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,> I don't want to kill the buds even a little. > Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.35,0:12:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,> In the palace? > In the palace? Then, is it an Imperial Conference?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.56,0:12:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,> There are cycads here as well
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.35,0:13:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,> Thus, from 23:50 on August 9th, an Imperial Conference was convened to ask for the Emperor's decision and decree.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.80,0:13:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The appearance of the ministers at the supreme Council varies, but their thoughts were just the result of the Imperial Conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.07,0:13:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,> Mr. Shimomura, I would like to ask you. Has the Emperor ever been asked for his decree like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.97,0:13:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,> No. Up until now, even though it was a sacred decision, it was said that the opinions summarized by his vassals would be approved.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.80,0:13:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,His Majesty the emperor himself has not made a decision like this. There is a lot of fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.97,0:13:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,> Hmm. After all. > It is unprecedented. The decision the people have made so far will be painful,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.42,0:14:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,> The stars are beautiful. > At this time, what kind of story did you tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.90,0:14:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,> Cycad. > Oh, so that's what you were talking about at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.21,0:14:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,> In other words, no matter what happens to the old leaves, if the roots are not withered, new shoots will come out again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.21,0:14:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,> Whatever happens to the old leaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.49,0:14:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,> Thank you for waiting. The Supreme War Leaders Conference is now over. From now on, we will hold a cabinet meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.80,0:15:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,> Each member gave their opinions one by one, and after that, we received a sacred decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.59,0:15:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The gist of the words is that when looking at the situation in the nation, continuing the war not only destroys Japan,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.76,0:15:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,but also makes the worlds human beings even more unhappy. He said that he would accept the three countries declaration, and end the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.32,0:15:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, his Majesty had words of compassion for the Army and Navy soldiers, casualties, and victims of the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.80,0:16:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus the decree came down. However, some members of the Army and Navy have voiced opposition to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.97,0:16:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,this decision regarding the conditions under which they would accept the Tripartite Joint Declaration.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.87,0:16:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, on the 14th, an Imperial conference was held again with the attendance of all ministers, and unconditional surrender was finally decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.14,0:16:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,> Excuse me for the last time. Is this the original plan of an imperial edict?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.01,0:16:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,> Yeah. It is quite difficult to want everyone in the nation to understand what will happen when the imperial decision comes down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.97,0:16:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,> How will you announce it? > Newspapers and radio broadcasts. I will do both, so it will be up to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.35,0:17:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,> That One
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.21,0:17:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,> What happened? > Is it Jewel Voice Broadcasting?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.97,0:17:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,> Yeah. > Some officers are aiming to prevent it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.11,0:17:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,> Is that so? Thank you for letting me know. > Please take some measures.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.66,0:17:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,> There is no countermeasure. If this is his Majesty's life-threatening decree, then I will protect it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.90,0:17:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,During this time, when I received his Majesty's decree, I was deeply impressed. This final decision is life-threatening.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.80,0:17:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time of the final decision, there will be a lot of commotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.35,0:17:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It means that you can always make a decision to return to the beginning if you risk your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.18,0:17:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,> I also made a lot of noise. > However, everyone thinks it's good for the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.94,0:18:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,However, there are many things that are good for the country. It is the decision of the highest officer to make no doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.49,0:18:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,> Is your future life-threatening job to convey his Majesty's words to the Japanese people?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.18,0:18:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,> Yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.32,0:18:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,> 10:00 am on August 14th. An unprecedented in Japanese history "Jewel Voice Broadcast" was recorded.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.07,0:18:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,> Mr. Yabe, you and I are the only ones who controlled the recording board in the basement of the Imperial Household Ministry. We may be caught tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.45,0:19:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,> What? > I wont talk even if it costs my life. I don't want you to break either.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.97,0:19:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,> Of course
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.59,0:19:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,> Are you the Minister of State Shimomuria? > It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.80,0:19:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,> Alright, take him to the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.63,0:19:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,> Hiroshi Shimomura? Please come for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.35,0:20:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,> I brought Hiroshi Shimomura > Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.94,0:20:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,> You are Hiroshi Shimomura, the president of the Information Bureau, right? > That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.28,0:20:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,> I've been checking the car now, but I didn't find the recording board for Jewel Voice. Where did you hide it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.04,0:20:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,> Why do you want that recording board? > I want His Majesty to spend another three or four days thinking it over and that His Majesty can trust the army.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.35,0:20:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,> Can you do that in three or four days? > Please tell me anyways. Where is the recording board?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.18,0:20:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,> I can't say.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.28,0:20:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,> Then, would you like me to search your body?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.45,0:20:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,> At that time, Governor Shimomura was fearful for his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.52,0:20:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, he envisioned a defensive mainland operation at the behest of the Minister of the Imperial Japanese Army Anan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.35,0:21:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Life-threatening alone is not an accurate decision. What is the decision of the highest level?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.87,0:21:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,> Stop it. It's not good to deal with Governor Shimomura now. He won't open his mouth anyway, so go look for it at the Imperial Household Ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.80,0:21:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,> Yes > Keep all of them in this place until we finish the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.83,0:21:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,> Yes, I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.28,0:21:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,> They urged the Broadcasting Association, Director Yabe, to take him to the back of the Imperial Household Ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.11,0:21:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask where the recording board was, but he didn't say.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.14,0:21:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, some rebel officers invaded the broadcasting station before dawn on the 15th and tried to broadcast
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.11,0:21:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,by themselves, but they did not succeed. They pulled up to the imperial palace and decided to commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.11,0:22:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,<The Jewel Voice Broadcast>
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.11,0:22:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,"enduring the unendurable and suffering what is insufferable."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.83,0:22:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,> At the time, the superlative decision was life-threatening. > I think so too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.63,0:22:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,> But that alone does not seem to make a real decision, Everyone was fearful of course, His Majesty, Anan, Yoneuchi, Togo as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.35,0:22:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But why is everyone making a different decision although they are all fearful?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.14,0:23:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The difference is the protection of the national polity. Even if we say "Japan", it exists because the country and the people remain.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.49,0:23:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They haven't grasped this idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.70,0:23:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a country, there is no national polity. Now it's important to keep that country. If only the country is left, Japan will surely sprout again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.21,0:23:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an eye that looks closely at the theme.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.90,0:23:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What's more, in order to see it, it is important to look forward to the future without being bound by your own position.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.42,0:23:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a real decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.32,0:23:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and a courageous one.
